						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the temple of Śrī Rāma.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1094, Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land to the temple of Sōmēśvara-Mahādēva by Maṇḍana, the son of Paṇḍa-nāyaka Sōmana-Peggaḍa, for the merit of his parents.</p>						

						</summary>
